  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior | Occupational Therapist (Therapy Hub)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for Senior/ Occupational Therapists to be part of our dynamic, interprofessional, collaborative team of Allied Health Professionals, which includes Occupational Therapists, Speech Therapists, and Physiotherapists.</p><p>As a therapy hub, we serve the community across various settings, including early intervention centre, special education school, day activity centre and sheltered workshop. We are committed to supporting our clients' ability to participate in the home and community.</p><p>If you are passionate about making a meaningful impact, we invite you to join us in delivering person-centered care and holistic rehabilitation.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assess and identify the individual needs of clients and formulate, develop and implement appropriate individualized therapy programmes;</li><li>Assess and monitor therapy outcomes;</li><li>Liaise with various disciplines involved in the integration process;</li><li>Refer clients to the respective specialists for consultation and intervention;</li><li>Able to work with Allied Health Professional Group team in formulating service delivery to clients; and</li><li>Senior OT may be assigned with supervisory duties</li></ul><p>Job Requirements:</p><ul><li>Recognised Degree in Occupational Therapy (listed in <a href=\"https://www.healthprofessionals.gov.sg/ahpc/apply-to-be-a-registered-allied-health-professional/lists-of-recognised-qualifications\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.healthprofessionals.gov.sg/ahpc/apply-to-be-a-registered-allied-health-professional/lists-of-recognised-qualifications</a>)</li><li>Registered as a Full Registrant with the Allied Health Professional Council in Singapore</li><li>Candidates with 3–5 years of experience working with children with Autism are preferred.</li></ul>",
